    <div class='collapse' id='collapseLibraryInfo'>
        <p>
        Our mission is to help computational modelers at all levels engage in the
        <a href='https://www.openmodelingfoundation.org'>establishment and adoption of community standards</a> and
        <a href='{{ slugurl("guides-to-good-practice") }}'>good practices</a> for developing and sharing computational
        models. Model authors can freely publish their model source code in the Computational Model Library alongside
        narrative documentation, open science metadata, and other emerging norms that facilitate software
        citation, archival, interoperability, and reuse. Model authors can also request that their model code be
        <a href='/reviews/'>peer reviewed</a> to receive a DOI.
        </p>
        <p>
        All users of models published in the library <b>must cite model authors</b> when they use and benefit
        from their code. 
        </p>
    </div>
    <p>
